<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 2:59PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central
Anderson and central Pickens Counties through 330 PM EDT...
At 258 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles north of Pickens, or 4 miles south of Table Rock State Park,
moving south at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Easley, Pickens, Powdersville, Piedmont, Central, Liberty, Norris,
Table Rock State Park, Pendleton and Jocassee Gorges.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
